WEBVTT

00:36.161 --> 00:38.955
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

00:40.040 --> 00:43.376
AS GROUP
COMPANY FALL RETREAT

00:57.182 --> 00:59.100
You know, when I'm in a good mood,

00:59.809 --> 01:00.977
I eat vegetables.

01:07.692 --> 01:09.069
Have you eaten yet, Ye-ji?

01:09.694 --> 01:11.071
Eat lots of vegetables.

01:18.787 --> 01:20.497
There are no vegetables.

01:25.502 --> 01:28.338
THE LOYAL CATERING

01:32.592 --> 01:33.718
Salute!

02:19.055 --> 02:21.349
-Hello, can I get your name?
-Byeon Eun-a.

02:37.657 --> 02:38.867
Eun-a!

02:38.950 --> 02:40.535
Eun-a, over here.

02:56.509 --> 02:58.845
XIMFIT WILL ANALYZE EMOTIONS
YOU DIDN'T EVEN KNOW YOU HAD

04:06.454 --> 04:09.499
I was categorized
as an unemployed male in his forties.

04:09.582 --> 04:10.792
What about you, Eun-a?

04:10.875 --> 04:12.919
A female in her thirties
with psychological issues.

04:15.004 --> 04:15.964
I'm serious.

04:16.047 --> 04:19.634
Did Lee Jun-hwan
specifically describe you that way?

04:19.717 --> 04:21.511
No, someone else introduced me to this.

04:22.553 --> 04:24.973
Nobody at work knows
I'm wearing this watch.

04:25.056 --> 04:26.432
Oh, right, I see.

04:27.725 --> 04:30.853
They said this could help people
with psychological issues.

04:35.608 --> 04:37.485
Psychological issues?

04:42.115 --> 04:44.242
You've got a word
that makes your heart pound, don't you?

04:46.244 --> 04:47.578
I had no idea

04:47.662 --> 04:49.914
the word "unemployed"
would make my heart pound so much.

04:50.540 --> 04:54.794
When my heart rate goes up,
and warning beeps go off,

04:54.877 --> 04:56.296
my heart pounds even more.

04:56.379 --> 04:58.131
Knowing that it's pounding
makes it pound more.

04:59.507 --> 05:00.633
It feels like,

05:01.634 --> 05:02.677
"Oh, I've been caught."

05:04.095 --> 05:05.555
You haven't experienced it yet, have you?

05:07.265 --> 05:09.767
You'll discover a word
that makes your heart pound.

05:11.102 --> 05:12.895
Just hearing that makes my heart race.

05:14.188 --> 05:16.274
So you do have a word
that makes your heart pound?

05:17.567 --> 05:18.609
I have too many.

05:19.861 --> 05:21.195
They're not words

05:22.238 --> 05:23.948
-so much as they are names.
-Names?

05:24.532 --> 05:25.366
The names

05:26.409 --> 05:27.618
of the men who left me.

05:29.120 --> 05:30.163
"Men"?

05:30.830 --> 05:31.789
Plural?

05:32.874 --> 05:35.501
Whenever I hear the name of anyone
who wrote me off,

05:37.045 --> 05:38.755
my heart pounds immediately.

05:38.838 --> 05:41.049
Gosh, the mere thought makes it pound.

05:42.800 --> 05:43.676
I don't react

05:44.594 --> 05:46.179
to names at all.

05:46.846 --> 05:48.097
Your relationships must be nice and neat.

05:48.723 --> 05:50.808
They're actually nice and messed up

05:52.018 --> 05:54.103
because everyone has written me off.

05:56.856 --> 05:58.608
All names disrespect me,

05:58.691 --> 06:00.234
and I disrespect all names.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.863
Thanks to this watch,

06:03.946 --> 06:08.785
I've realized that I don't like anyone
or anything in this world.

06:08.868 --> 06:10.453
Except for food.

06:10.536 --> 06:12.830
Food is the only thing I respect and love.

06:14.248 --> 06:17.710
My favorite writing is what's on a menu.

06:18.336 --> 06:20.463
There's nothing more beautiful than that.

06:23.883 --> 06:24.967
Wearing this watch

06:25.843 --> 06:27.178
made one thing very clear.

06:27.762 --> 06:30.473
I'm a destructive person.

06:36.813 --> 06:37.730
You see…

06:39.440 --> 06:42.193
there was a moment
that made me really trust this watch.

06:42.276 --> 06:44.612
I went to a café the other day,

06:44.695 --> 06:47.573
and all of a sudden,
I heard a screech and a thud.

06:49.408 --> 06:51.702
I'd never heard anything like that
so up close before.

06:51.786 --> 06:53.496
-Oh no.
-I didn't see you.

06:53.579 --> 06:54.747
I'll have my insurance take care of it.

06:54.831 --> 06:57.166
My heart was pounding like crazy
from the shock,

06:57.250 --> 06:59.961
so when this vibrated,
I didn't even think twice.

07:00.044 --> 07:03.381
I figured it'd be "fear" or "shock."

07:03.464 --> 07:05.508
But do you know what it said?

07:12.598 --> 07:14.267
EXCITED

07:14.350 --> 07:15.309
"Excited."

07:15.977 --> 07:17.478
No way.

07:17.562 --> 07:19.647
I had to cover it up before anyone saw it.

07:24.527 --> 07:27.196
I just accepted it at that point.

07:27.780 --> 07:30.074
That's right. I was excited.

07:31.951 --> 07:33.244
Jeez, Hwang Dong-man.

07:36.164 --> 07:39.000
There was a world leaders' summit
not too long ago.

07:39.083 --> 07:42.003
I woke up with a cold that morning,

07:42.086 --> 07:45.173
but I still worked a catering gig
for a 500-person luncheon

07:45.256 --> 07:46.924
and then taught a class in the evening.

07:47.008 --> 07:49.051
I barely made it home and just collapsed,

07:49.135 --> 07:50.511
but I had to look at my phone.

07:50.595 --> 07:51.512
Yeah.

07:52.013 --> 07:52.930
I think

07:53.431 --> 07:56.058
I'll check my phone even on my deathbed.

07:56.142 --> 07:59.228
Anyway, I was on my phone,
and I see there's been a terrorist attack.

07:59.812 --> 08:02.023
So I jumped up and turned on the TV.

08:02.106 --> 08:05.860
I saw special forces rushing in
and heard gunfire.

08:05.943 --> 08:09.238
And I thought to myself,
"If all those world leaders were to die,

08:09.322 --> 08:11.491
the world would finally fall apart."

08:13.159 --> 08:16.078
I'm watching in shock,
and you know what popped up on my watch?

08:16.746 --> 08:17.705
I think I know.

08:17.788 --> 08:19.040
"Thrilled."

08:20.208 --> 08:21.292
Oh jeez.

08:21.375 --> 08:23.252
I wasn't watching out of concern.

08:23.878 --> 08:25.713
I was about to die from exhaustion,

08:25.796 --> 08:27.632
but suddenly, I was wide awake
and not tired at all.

08:29.008 --> 08:32.011
I forgot I was tired and kept watching.

08:33.513 --> 08:35.890
They rescued everyone,
and the terrorists were captured alive.

08:35.973 --> 08:38.392
-You know what popped up?
-Beep.

08:38.476 --> 08:41.020
No, I can't. I don't want to get it right.

08:41.604 --> 08:42.855
"Disappointed"?

08:47.360 --> 08:49.403
How could there be no casualties?

08:49.487 --> 08:52.240
I was exhausted,
but I watched it till the end.

08:52.323 --> 08:54.158
I deserved to see a dramatic ending.

08:54.784 --> 08:56.494
That's just the guy I am, and I accept it.

08:56.577 --> 08:58.162
This is who I am.

08:58.246 --> 08:59.455
Guilty as charged.

08:59.539 --> 09:02.041
Words like "love" or "peace"

09:02.792 --> 09:04.794
bore me to death.

09:05.711 --> 09:08.172
But "revenge," "destruction,"
or "retribution"?

09:08.256 --> 09:10.800
When I hear such words, my eyes sparkle.

09:11.384 --> 09:13.553
The best part about wearing this
was when I realized,

09:13.636 --> 09:15.096
"Hey, Hwang Dong-man."

09:15.763 --> 09:17.223
"You're a destructive person."

09:17.306 --> 09:19.809
It laid it out for me, nice and simple.

09:20.434 --> 09:23.896
So I decided to stop pretending
to be a good person.

09:30.695 --> 09:32.280
When Park Gyeong-se's movie tanked…

09:34.824 --> 09:36.284
I was truly happy.

09:36.867 --> 09:38.119
SISTER VENGEANCE

09:38.202 --> 09:39.745
Bad reviews were pouring in.

09:40.454 --> 09:41.831
And it was

09:42.415 --> 09:43.416
really brutal.

09:44.625 --> 09:46.627
There was a certain satisfaction
in knowing

09:46.711 --> 09:49.338
the whole country realized
just how lame he really was.

09:51.132 --> 09:53.718
I cooked myself some fresh rice for once,

09:53.801 --> 09:56.762
and danced for the first time in my life.

09:56.846 --> 10:01.058
I felt guilt-free satisfaction
in someone else's misfortune.

10:03.728 --> 10:05.438
I realized, "So this is peace."

10:05.521 --> 10:07.231
Now, you might ask,

10:08.190 --> 10:09.358
"Aren't you two close?"

10:09.442 --> 10:10.276
Nope.

10:10.359 --> 10:12.445
We need to clarify the meaning of "close."

10:12.528 --> 10:14.905
We've just known each other
for a long time.

10:14.989 --> 10:18.075
We're well acquainted,
but we don't like each other.

10:18.784 --> 10:19.910
We used to be close.

10:21.704 --> 10:23.331
Back when we were all the same.

10:23.956 --> 10:25.666
When we were all nobodies

10:26.792 --> 10:29.253
sitting around together,
roasting other people's movies.

10:29.337 --> 10:32.506
Park Gyeong-se was the one
who talked the most trash back then.

10:33.299 --> 10:35.509
This is why it's getting bad reviews!

10:36.135 --> 10:39.138
There's no storyline, and it's just noisy!

10:39.221 --> 10:40.389
What's this even about?

10:40.473 --> 10:41.599
Someone explain it to me.

10:43.559 --> 10:45.269
One by one, they made their debut.

10:45.353 --> 10:47.229
Look, over here. The transitions.

10:47.313 --> 10:48.898
-Jeez, did you see that?
-Damn it.

10:49.440 --> 10:51.150
You're going to break the TV!

10:53.486 --> 10:55.946
Now, the seven of them
get together to talk trash without me.

10:57.615 --> 10:59.116
Whenever I show up…

10:59.200 --> 11:00.076
Hey, you're here.

11:00.826 --> 11:02.161
They're indifferent.

11:03.829 --> 11:07.750
Like I'm not on their level anymore,
and they don't see me as worth debating.

11:10.211 --> 11:11.379
What a bunch of jerks.

11:16.008 --> 11:17.635
I'm starting to get upset.

11:21.764 --> 11:22.848
In any case,

11:22.932 --> 11:23.933
I, Hwang Dong-man,

11:25.476 --> 11:26.769
am a destructive person.

11:36.278 --> 11:37.446
You seem like someone

11:39.073 --> 11:41.617
with a thousand doors wide open.

11:48.374 --> 11:51.210
Imagine everyone
had a thousand doors inside them.

11:52.378 --> 11:56.340
Reading something written by someone
who hasn't even opened a single door

11:56.424 --> 11:57.591
is so boring and suffocating.

11:58.968 --> 12:03.681
But reading a screenplay by someone
with a few doors open grabs my attention.

12:04.432 --> 12:05.474
You seem like someone

12:07.184 --> 12:10.020
who's got all a thousand doors wide open.

12:17.236 --> 12:18.988
Then why'd you say those things

12:20.030 --> 12:21.031
last time?

12:22.074 --> 12:23.534
In front of Mr. Choi.

12:24.452 --> 12:27.955
The protagonist in Weather Maker
didn't feel like you.

12:30.082 --> 12:33.085
Well, that's because the protagonist
has to be cooler than me.

12:34.712 --> 12:36.505
You're way cooler.

12:44.013 --> 12:45.306
You're much more raw…

12:47.308 --> 12:48.350
and much warmer.

13:40.694 --> 13:42.571
I thought I'd feel better

13:43.113 --> 13:44.490
if I wore this watch.

13:45.324 --> 13:48.035
Like, "Oh, I'm feeling down right now.
Let's change that."

13:48.536 --> 13:50.162
I thought I could change my mood.

13:50.871 --> 13:52.206
But turns out, I can't.

13:52.289 --> 13:53.165
Nope.

13:53.249 --> 13:55.626
You can never force
your emotions to change.

13:56.252 --> 13:59.046
When you feel down,
pick up a 500-won coin on the street.

14:01.549 --> 14:02.925
Like a small win.

14:03.551 --> 14:06.303
That's what can change your mood.

14:07.263 --> 14:08.639
Willpower can't make that happen.

14:09.181 --> 14:11.308
That's why I take off running
from here every day.

14:12.434 --> 14:16.647
Here's to the joy of setting a new record!

14:53.809 --> 14:55.019
YOUR CURRENT SPEED
24 KM/H

14:55.603 --> 14:56.562
A new record!

15:12.786 --> 15:13.871
Have a good night.

15:13.954 --> 15:14.955
-Good night.
-Bye.

15:33.390 --> 15:35.267
HWANG DONG-MAN AND HIS BROTHER
NOT ALLOWED

15:35.351 --> 15:36.518
Writing a noir? Why?

15:36.602 --> 15:38.354
-Why not?
-Don't do it.

15:40.147 --> 15:40.981
There you are.

15:41.065 --> 15:43.233
You traitors.

15:44.151 --> 15:47.363
You having fun drinking at a place
your friend's banned from?

15:48.614 --> 15:49.782
Lee Jun-hwan!

15:50.282 --> 15:52.117
You might as well come out.

15:52.201 --> 15:53.827
Your shadow is a dead giveaway!

15:59.708 --> 16:00.960
Hey!

16:02.544 --> 16:05.047
-Jeez! Hey, pull him over.
-Is he insane?

16:05.756 --> 16:07.633
Jeez, you're such a handful.

16:08.926 --> 16:09.927
What the heck?

16:10.552 --> 16:12.262
-What are you doing?
-So then…

16:28.320 --> 16:29.238
Salute, sir.

16:31.865 --> 16:34.451
Did you know that Hitler resides in him?

16:35.744 --> 16:37.287
He has a desire

16:37.371 --> 16:41.417
to get rid of anyone
he finds incompetent or disapproves of.

16:42.292 --> 16:44.211
A strong urge to clear them out.

16:45.879 --> 16:46.755
Salute, sir!

16:56.181 --> 16:58.726
…and deliberately made time for us.

16:58.809 --> 16:59.810
Excuse me.

17:00.310 --> 17:01.145
Hye-jin.

17:02.521 --> 17:03.355
Just a moment.

17:04.648 --> 17:05.482
Tell me.

17:06.150 --> 17:07.943
Is there anyone you actually approve of?

17:08.027 --> 17:09.820
Everyone on the subway sucks, don't they?

17:10.821 --> 17:12.114
And they're all ugly.

17:13.073 --> 17:14.908
Might as well get rid of them
and live alone then.

17:17.911 --> 17:18.871
Does this mean

17:19.621 --> 17:21.248
I can also get rid of something

17:22.041 --> 17:24.835
that I don't approve of?

17:29.048 --> 17:31.258
I've been patient enough, you bastard!

17:33.719 --> 17:35.012
Hey, get back here!

17:36.764 --> 17:37.598
Hey!

17:40.809 --> 17:41.727
You little bastard.

17:42.269 --> 17:44.438
Damn it. You punk!

17:44.521 --> 17:47.357
You started this, so this is what you get!

17:48.275 --> 17:49.693
What the hell is he saying?

17:50.277 --> 17:51.111
That little…

17:51.612 --> 17:52.821
Hwang Dong-man!

17:59.244 --> 18:01.872
This is the first time
anyone has come to my place.

18:01.955 --> 18:03.082
Wait, Jun-hwan's been here.

18:03.624 --> 18:05.417
Well, you're the first woman to visit.

18:05.501 --> 18:07.711
I think canned ham tastes better
than pork.

18:07.795 --> 18:11.465
If I had to choose between ham and pork
to take to a deserted island,

18:12.299 --> 18:13.217
I'd choose ham.

18:16.762 --> 18:17.596
Two eggs?

18:18.180 --> 18:19.014
Four?

18:21.475 --> 18:23.143
-Four eggs.
-Okay.

18:26.438 --> 18:27.523
One.

18:28.857 --> 18:29.858
Two.

18:34.822 --> 18:35.823
Four, right?

18:39.701 --> 18:40.619
The perfect trio.

18:47.000 --> 18:47.835
The perfect trio.

18:56.844 --> 18:57.678
What?

18:59.596 --> 19:00.556
Watch yourself.

19:02.057 --> 19:04.143
Or else I'll really lock you up
in a mental hospital.

19:06.979 --> 19:08.063
And the maintenance fee?

19:08.814 --> 19:09.898
I paid it.

19:11.984 --> 19:13.861
Don't drink on an empty stomach.

19:18.490 --> 19:20.659
SISTER VENGEANCE
STAGE GREETING

19:21.952 --> 19:24.788
The entire cast pushed themselves
to the breaking point.

19:24.872 --> 19:26.415
I hope you all enjoy the film,

19:26.498 --> 19:31.170
and please spread the word
about Sister Vengeance.

19:31.253 --> 19:32.504
Thank you!

19:35.883 --> 19:37.676
Hello, this is Jang Mi-ran.

19:37.759 --> 19:39.261
WE'RE HERE TO SEE YOU, MI-RAN!

19:39.887 --> 19:41.597
My body didn't actually break,

19:41.680 --> 19:43.015
but my arm did get wrecked.

19:44.349 --> 19:47.436
I worked so hard I couldn't tell
if I was sawing with my arm

19:47.519 --> 19:50.147
or sawing my arm off.

19:50.230 --> 19:52.149
Did you see
the weekend screening schedule?

19:52.774 --> 19:55.986
We need more afternoon showings
on the weekends.

19:56.069 --> 19:58.030
No one will watch it
if it's just mornings and nights.

19:58.572 --> 20:01.200
That's up to the distribution team.
You know the theaters don't listen to me.

20:01.742 --> 20:03.577
They only add showings for movies
that are selling.

20:05.120 --> 20:06.038
Then how about

20:06.872 --> 20:08.248
we hand out free tickets?

20:09.291 --> 20:11.210
Just 3,000.

20:11.919 --> 20:13.837
All right, I'll get to it.

20:15.005 --> 20:15.839
Okay.

20:18.300 --> 20:20.260
I'm the one who took the loss,

20:21.303 --> 20:22.804
so why are they the ones bitching?

20:51.166 --> 20:54.586
Director Park, I think your debut film
was your best work.

21:09.268 --> 21:11.061
-It's time to go now.
-Let's go.

21:16.692 --> 21:17.818
Man, these reviews…

21:23.657 --> 21:24.950
-Hey, it's Jang Mi-ran!
-Wow!

21:36.128 --> 21:37.879
I'm Director Park Gyeong-se.

21:41.633 --> 21:43.218
I just liked filmmaking…

21:44.970 --> 21:46.555
not knowing how tough it was.

21:52.978 --> 21:54.730
We worked really hard on this film.

22:15.417 --> 22:17.419
"I got mad and looked up
the director's films."

22:17.502 --> 22:20.464
"I haven't watched a single one.
I'll know to skip his work from now on."

22:22.549 --> 22:25.052
"A movie that spends the whole time

22:25.135 --> 22:27.471
pretending to be cool and meaningful."

22:31.266 --> 22:32.642
"This is the first movie

22:33.477 --> 22:35.103
I've ever walked out of."

22:38.231 --> 22:39.191
"Hey, Director."

22:40.233 --> 22:41.443
"If you have a conscience,

22:42.819 --> 22:43.904
refund my 15,000 won

22:45.030 --> 22:46.490
for the ticket."

22:48.116 --> 22:49.242
"Refund my 15,000 won."

22:50.994 --> 22:51.995
My movie…

22:53.455 --> 22:55.165
makes people want a refund.

22:55.248 --> 22:56.500
You can skip the movie…

22:57.125 --> 22:58.835
You can skip the movie…

22:58.919 --> 22:59.961
You can skip the movie…

23:01.046 --> 23:03.340
You can skip the movie and read about it
in group chats.

23:06.301 --> 23:07.427
"A movie so dull

23:08.303 --> 23:11.056
that you don't even get mad
when people text or take calls."

23:13.141 --> 23:14.434
"…when people text or take calls."

23:15.685 --> 23:17.145
"I feel like murdering my friend

23:17.896 --> 23:19.356
who recommended this movie."

23:20.065 --> 23:21.024
My movie

23:21.858 --> 23:23.401
drives people to murder.

23:24.778 --> 23:25.737
My movie

23:26.530 --> 23:29.282
drives people to murder.

23:36.039 --> 23:37.207
Gyeong-se isn't answering.

23:37.958 --> 23:39.251
Leave him alone.

23:40.293 --> 23:43.338
I never liked it when people
tried to make me feel better

23:44.381 --> 23:45.257
by texting or calling.

23:47.759 --> 23:49.177
You should've told me before I sent it.

23:50.720 --> 23:51.555
Darn it.

23:52.180 --> 23:53.181
THE EIGHT CLUB

23:54.266 --> 23:55.267
Huh?

23:56.184 --> 23:57.102
Did you know

23:57.727 --> 23:59.187
Gyeong-se was in the group chat?

23:59.688 --> 24:01.773
Yeong-su probably added him back in.

24:01.857 --> 24:04.609
When did he do that?

24:08.655 --> 24:09.698
Damn it!

24:10.323 --> 24:11.408
Wait, this is…

24:12.284 --> 24:15.453
Gyeong-se keeps leaving every time
he's added back in,

24:15.537 --> 24:18.748
so Dong-man probably sent these messages,
thinking he'd left again.

24:18.832 --> 24:20.959
HOW DID THIS MOVIE
EVEN MAKE IT OUT INTO THE WORLD?

24:21.042 --> 24:23.003
I GUESS IT COMES DOWN TO
WHETHER YOUR WIFE IS AN EXECUTIVE PRODUCER

24:23.587 --> 24:25.213
Hwang Dong-man, that bastard.

24:25.297 --> 24:27.257
Why would he say this in our group chat?

24:27.340 --> 24:30.218
So no one noticed all the messages
he's been sending?

24:30.302 --> 24:31.553
Who bothers to read them?

24:31.636 --> 24:33.805
They're always about what he ate

24:33.889 --> 24:35.682
or what he watched or whatever.

24:35.765 --> 24:37.100
He sends dozens of messages.

24:37.184 --> 24:39.686
I just go in to clear the unread count.

24:40.395 --> 24:42.689
-You don't read them either!
-Oh jeez.

24:43.648 --> 24:44.566
What's Gyeong-se doing?

24:46.484 --> 24:47.819
He went hiking in Jirisan.

24:50.822 --> 24:52.574
In any case,

24:53.325 --> 24:55.785
Gyeong-se can never see this.

24:56.411 --> 24:58.121
The unread count is still at one,

24:58.747 --> 24:59.623
so he hasn't read them.

24:59.706 --> 25:01.458
Just leave him alone for now.

25:01.541 --> 25:04.961
Don't call and tell him to leave the chat
without reading the messages.

25:05.045 --> 25:07.088
That'll just make him go in and read them.

25:07.881 --> 25:08.798
Just leave him alone.

25:08.882 --> 25:10.342
Leave him alone

25:10.425 --> 25:12.469
and pray that he'll leave the group chat.

25:13.053 --> 25:16.014
Hwang Dong-man, that little punk.

25:50.340 --> 25:51.174
What?

25:56.221 --> 25:57.055
Yeong-su.

25:58.056 --> 25:59.432
The number disappeared.

26:00.475 --> 26:01.309
What?

26:16.324 --> 26:19.703
Hwang Dong-man, you fucking bastard!

26:20.704 --> 26:22.872
You fucking bastard!

26:27.752 --> 26:29.546
-Here, Mr. Hwang.
-What?

26:34.259 --> 26:35.260
Thank you.

26:35.885 --> 26:37.971
Yeah, this one tastes the best.

26:38.513 --> 26:40.515
It's the bestseller at our store.

26:42.517 --> 26:44.477
-Tell your mother I said thank you.
-I will.

26:46.855 --> 26:49.983
I got up early today and did some writing
for the first time in a while.

26:50.066 --> 26:51.151
I was totally focused.

26:52.110 --> 26:54.070
I feel guilty for trying hard these days

26:54.154 --> 26:56.573
because I swore to live a worthless life.

26:57.741 --> 26:59.784
I can't help it because I'm having fun.

27:02.370 --> 27:04.039
But don't forget to live a worthless life.

27:04.122 --> 27:05.457
Right, live a worthless life.

27:07.667 --> 27:09.127
-Hello.
-Hello.

27:09.210 --> 27:10.837
Hey, eat before you go in!

27:11.880 --> 27:14.591
No change in advance ticket sales
despite giving out free tickets?

27:15.258 --> 27:16.134
None at all.

27:18.678 --> 27:20.263
Forget the marketing, then.

27:21.181 --> 27:22.724
Stop wasting money

27:22.807 --> 27:23.975
and just let it go.

27:26.936 --> 27:30.148
Who called the opening week numbers
for Sister Vengeance?

27:33.318 --> 27:37.072
The current number is about 310,000.

27:37.155 --> 27:38.198
No one came close, right?

27:40.158 --> 27:41.618
Someone called 300,000.

27:45.413 --> 27:46.247
Who?

27:47.540 --> 27:48.625
Ms. Byeon Eun-a.

28:02.931 --> 28:05.809
Lucky you for guessing correctly.

28:15.652 --> 28:17.362
What about the numbers for that one?

28:24.661 --> 28:26.246
Don't hold back. Just tell me.

28:31.084 --> 28:33.962
Can't you give it to me straight for once?

28:34.796 --> 28:36.381
How frustrating.

28:44.347 --> 28:46.641
I'm meeting Actor Song at Agit tonight.

28:46.725 --> 28:47.726
Come with me.

28:47.809 --> 28:49.352
Agit is like heaven these days

28:49.436 --> 28:51.354
now that Hwang Dong-man,
that pile of crap, isn't there.

28:51.438 --> 28:53.273
It feels like we've cleared out
ten years' worth of trash.

28:53.773 --> 28:55.692
He should've been banned a long time ago.

28:55.775 --> 28:58.528
But he keeps coming back,
only to be kicked out again.

28:58.611 --> 28:59.946
He's insane.

29:03.783 --> 29:04.743
Did you just sigh?

29:09.622 --> 29:10.707
No.

29:17.172 --> 29:18.965
Yes, you did. Why?

29:22.218 --> 29:23.219
Why did you sigh?

29:27.307 --> 29:29.017
What you said was too harsh.

29:30.810 --> 29:32.562
"Ten years' worth of trash."

29:34.606 --> 29:36.274
"A walking corpse."

29:36.858 --> 29:39.402
If I remember correctly,
you used to talk pretty harshly too.

29:40.028 --> 29:41.780
But you've lost your edge these days.

29:43.406 --> 29:45.408
You keep siding with Hwang Dong-man,

29:46.242 --> 29:48.369
but don't call us the bad guys

29:48.453 --> 29:49.537
without seeing what he's like.

29:53.208 --> 29:54.292
I'll see for myself.

30:06.846 --> 30:08.640
Did you see her talk back to me?

30:09.891 --> 30:14.354
I promoted her from office assistant
because she had an eye for screenplays.

30:14.437 --> 30:17.524
Now she's full of herself
and still hasn't come to her senses,

30:17.607 --> 30:19.067
even after screwing up.

30:20.777 --> 30:24.447
Director Park Su-hyeon still rages
when her name comes up,

30:24.531 --> 30:26.282
saying she's a crazy you-know-what.

30:26.366 --> 30:27.742
You're pulling another all-nighter?

30:28.618 --> 30:29.953
Where are you getting stuck?

30:30.036 --> 30:31.412
Tell me, and I'll sort it out.

30:33.498 --> 30:35.542
Or come out for a quick drink.

30:36.626 --> 30:38.837
Sitting there won't solve anything.

30:38.920 --> 30:40.463
Come eat before you get back to it.

30:41.130 --> 30:42.048
Okay, bye.

30:45.134 --> 30:46.219
Hey, why are you here?

30:47.345 --> 30:48.346
You know how it is.

30:48.429 --> 30:49.848
It's technically a group chat,

30:49.931 --> 30:51.975
but Dong-man made it his own private chat.

30:52.892 --> 30:54.602
No one knew
he was saying things like that.

30:55.103 --> 30:57.438
Jun-hwan has been so busy writing

30:58.231 --> 31:00.149
that he didn't really read them either.

31:00.233 --> 31:01.067
Right.

31:01.651 --> 31:04.404
I'm sure Dong-man didn't know
you were in the group chat.

31:05.697 --> 31:07.407
Slow down.

31:13.037 --> 31:13.955
Man, I'm starving.

31:14.038 --> 31:14.914
Excuse me!

31:15.790 --> 31:18.501
Can I get a bowl of rice
and a rolled omelet?

31:20.753 --> 31:22.797
Make it a cheese rolled omelet, please!

31:22.881 --> 31:23.840
Sure thing.

31:25.383 --> 31:28.636
If I'd known this was a kimchi stew place,
I wouldn't have come.

31:30.680 --> 31:31.973
Should I give it a shot?

31:32.599 --> 31:33.433
Should I try it?

31:37.312 --> 31:38.271
Hey, come on.

31:41.107 --> 31:42.442
Jeez, man.

31:56.539 --> 31:57.916
Looks like you went hiking.

31:58.750 --> 32:00.376
It's best when you need to
clear your head.

32:03.171 --> 32:04.297
Hang in there.

32:04.380 --> 32:06.007
-You crazy punk.
-What?

32:06.090 --> 32:06.925
Here, drink this.

32:14.599 --> 32:15.433
Goodness gracious.

32:16.893 --> 32:17.727
You know,

32:18.895 --> 32:20.146
I can't even dream of hiking.

32:21.272 --> 32:23.983
I went to Seoraksan on a FAM tour
a long time ago,

32:24.067 --> 32:27.654
but I had to take a dump so bad
that I almost lost it running downhill.

32:27.737 --> 32:30.531
So now I break out in a cold sweat
whenever hiking comes up.

32:30.615 --> 32:32.575
I get anxious just looking at mountains.

32:33.368 --> 32:34.577
After that experience,

32:35.328 --> 32:37.789
I have nothing but respect for men
who go hiking.

32:38.790 --> 32:40.375
Which mountain did you go to?

32:46.798 --> 32:48.591
Why are you looking at me so lovingly?

32:49.968 --> 32:50.843
Tell me.

32:53.930 --> 32:55.348
You're enjoying this, aren't you?

32:56.975 --> 32:57.809
Yeah.

32:58.810 --> 32:59.644
Yeah.

33:00.269 --> 33:01.396
How did you know?

33:02.188 --> 33:03.523
I run around these days

33:04.148 --> 33:04.983
because I'm delighted.

33:08.653 --> 33:10.989
Put your hat back on.
You're hard to look at.

33:18.079 --> 33:20.498
I printed out the most scathing reviews

33:21.332 --> 33:23.376
and slowly read them out loud.

33:25.670 --> 33:27.171
I told myself to swallow them.

33:28.172 --> 33:29.966
If I couldn't swallow them,

33:30.717 --> 33:34.387
it felt like these bad reviews
would haunt me forever.

33:34.470 --> 33:36.514
So as I hiked up the mountain…

33:38.558 --> 33:41.144
I read each word carefully
and choked it down.

33:43.479 --> 33:45.314
Sweat streamed down my body,

33:46.274 --> 33:50.403
and I wasn't sure how I climbed up
as I kept mumbling the reviews.

33:50.486 --> 33:53.614
When I finally reached the summit
eight hours later,

33:54.490 --> 33:57.118
I thought I'd swallowed everything.

34:01.414 --> 34:03.332
Then I went into the group chat.

34:06.961 --> 34:07.795
That's right.

34:08.963 --> 34:10.548
I'm still in it.

34:13.760 --> 34:15.053
When I checked it,

34:16.345 --> 34:18.890
I saw the same words I had choked down.

34:20.808 --> 34:23.186
I guess you were impressed
with your own writing

34:23.269 --> 34:26.230
because it was posted
all over the internet.

34:26.314 --> 34:28.066
The words that went,

34:28.649 --> 34:30.109
"This is how good I am with words."

34:30.610 --> 34:33.404
"I guess whether
you become a director or not

34:35.198 --> 34:38.201
comes down to whether your wife
is an executive producer."

34:39.285 --> 34:41.913
"His wife spends a fortune
on her husband's hobby…"

34:46.125 --> 34:47.585
The one thing I was relieved about…

34:51.005 --> 34:53.549
was that Hye-jin
had already left the group chat.

34:56.052 --> 34:57.470
I noticed in the group chat…

34:59.847 --> 35:02.391
that one-third of the reviews
I had to choke down

35:03.893 --> 35:05.311
were written by you.

35:12.110 --> 35:17.240
I went to Jirisan at dawn
to force myself to choke down these words!

35:18.991 --> 35:21.202
Then I got so pissed
I ended up getting lost!

35:25.706 --> 35:28.126
I fought tooth and nail
to find my way back.

35:32.171 --> 35:35.800
I couldn't stand the idea of dying
without going straight for your throat,

35:37.260 --> 35:41.139
so I found a way down the mountain
like my life depended on it.

35:42.223 --> 35:43.266
-Hey.
-Gyeong-se.

35:49.605 --> 35:53.025
You asked how I had the nerve
to attend post-screening Q&amp;As.

35:54.068 --> 35:55.653
I feel like dying.

35:56.237 --> 35:57.864
Even the actors refuse to talk to me.

35:58.573 --> 36:00.283
I look at my phone in the waiting room.

36:00.908 --> 36:01.868
I feel like crying…

36:03.661 --> 36:05.163
being an outcast at my age.

36:08.416 --> 36:10.585
It's fine to go after me personally,

36:10.668 --> 36:15.256
but to attack my work like this
makes me feel like shit.

36:17.300 --> 36:18.968
I went through hell,
and I'm getting trashed.

36:19.051 --> 36:20.595
And the criticism is brutal.

36:22.430 --> 36:26.767
It feels like I've been stripped naked
and publicly dragged and shamed.

36:26.851 --> 36:28.477
I now feel compassion and respect

36:29.228 --> 36:31.856
for all the directors who came before me.

36:33.357 --> 36:35.651
They must've been
ripped to shreds like this…

36:37.528 --> 36:38.863
and been in so much pain.

36:42.450 --> 36:43.492
Hwang Dong-man,

36:44.744 --> 36:47.246
you've never been in the ring before.

36:47.830 --> 36:51.500
That's why you don't have any compassion
and just love it when people fail.

36:51.584 --> 36:52.919
That's the difference between us.

36:53.002 --> 36:54.503
It's a huge difference!

36:55.546 --> 36:56.964
It's the difference

36:58.007 --> 37:00.343
between a boxer
who's been beaten to a pulp in the ring

37:00.927 --> 37:03.804
and someone who's never stepped in one.

37:04.472 --> 37:08.142
It's like comparing someone already born
to someone not even born yet.

37:09.810 --> 37:10.728
Do you get it?

37:13.314 --> 37:14.148
You?

37:16.943 --> 37:18.569
You're just a nobody.

37:21.072 --> 37:21.948
Nothing.

37:22.031 --> 37:23.282
Nothing.

37:23.366 --> 37:24.700
Nothing!

37:28.537 --> 37:30.373
Park Gyeong-se, that bastard.

37:31.123 --> 37:35.586
How dare he? He calls that a movie?

37:36.128 --> 37:37.797
He hasn't made any good movies.

37:37.880 --> 37:39.215
That stupid bastard.

39:07.678 --> 39:08.679
Jin-man.

39:19.899 --> 39:21.067
What are you doing?

39:22.193 --> 39:23.569
Weren't you drinking?

39:26.906 --> 39:27.740
Jin-man.

39:31.202 --> 39:32.119
Come down.

39:40.628 --> 39:41.921
It's okay. Come down.

39:47.510 --> 39:48.803
You need to eat something.

39:50.596 --> 39:52.473
I'll make kimchi fried rice, so come down.

39:58.270 --> 39:59.730
Please come down, Jin-man.

40:59.874 --> 41:01.375
Hey, Jin-man.

41:02.084 --> 41:03.169
Want me to read you a poem?

41:04.295 --> 41:05.713
It's my favorite one.

41:07.548 --> 41:08.799
You wrote it

41:09.592 --> 41:12.928
when I was in middle school,
and I loved it so much

41:13.012 --> 41:15.431
that I hugged and kissed you
until you beat me up.

41:21.437 --> 41:22.271
The title is

41:23.481 --> 41:26.317
I Was a 0.2 mm Speck.

41:26.400 --> 41:27.735
EUNJEONG HIGH SCHOOL
LITERARY MAGAZINE

41:27.818 --> 41:29.528
A sperm is 0.001 mm

41:30.738 --> 41:32.323
An egg is 0.2 mm

41:34.033 --> 41:36.702
I mark the paper with a 0.2 mm dot

41:38.287 --> 41:39.371
That was me

41:40.998 --> 41:43.167
I was a 0.2 mm speck

41:46.253 --> 41:48.547
How did all this hatred fit in there?

41:50.257 --> 41:52.593
How did all this emptiness fit in there?

41:54.261 --> 41:55.596
My stomach churns

41:59.683 --> 42:02.269
A 0.2 mm fire ant passes by

42:03.646 --> 42:05.689
I crush it with my fingernail

42:09.318 --> 42:11.487
My hatred and emptiness

42:12.238 --> 42:13.906
Get crushed along with it

42:55.155 --> 42:56.073
Ms. Ko.

42:57.658 --> 42:58.576
Welcome.

42:59.493 --> 43:00.327
You're here.

43:00.411 --> 43:01.870
Congratulations!

43:01.954 --> 43:02.997
Congratulations.

43:04.790 --> 43:05.749
Thank you.

43:05.833 --> 43:07.042
It's good to see you.

43:07.835 --> 43:08.752
I'm excited to be here.

43:08.836 --> 43:11.380
KNOCK KNOCK KNOCK
BY MA JAE-YEONG

43:14.216 --> 43:15.342
I enjoyed it.

43:16.802 --> 43:20.347
Every character stands out,
and the story never loses momentum.

43:22.099 --> 43:23.017
Thank you.

43:23.100 --> 43:25.477
This is one of the top three screenplays
I've ever read.

43:28.522 --> 43:29.565
Thank you.

43:31.150 --> 43:33.444
And thanks for choosing Kopark Film
to handle the production.

43:34.028 --> 43:35.279
Of course, I'd choose Kopark Film.

43:39.575 --> 43:40.492
But you know what?

43:42.786 --> 43:45.456
I sense someone else
was involved in the screenplay.

43:49.835 --> 43:50.794
Oh.

43:53.088 --> 43:55.299
I just got some help

43:55.382 --> 43:56.300
from a friend.

43:59.219 --> 44:00.346
People like us can tell

44:01.347 --> 44:04.433
whether someone just gave advice
or actually had a hand in it.

44:07.102 --> 44:09.938
The way the characters talk
didn't come from you.

44:10.022 --> 44:11.065
It came from someone else.

44:12.483 --> 44:13.317
It was a woman.

44:15.944 --> 44:16.945
I know because I'm a woman.

44:17.863 --> 44:19.698
I can tell when a woman's lines

44:19.782 --> 44:21.575
were written by a man versus a woman.

44:21.659 --> 44:22.951
The same goes for you.

44:23.035 --> 44:25.788
You know when a man's lines
were written by a woman versus a man.

44:27.790 --> 44:30.959
There's an obvious female influence
in the screenplay.

44:31.585 --> 44:34.213
Is there a reason
she can't be the co-writer?

44:35.339 --> 44:37.883
Oh, she wasn't that involved.

44:37.966 --> 44:39.385
A co-writer?

44:40.094 --> 44:43.180
She just looked over it a bit,
but not enough to be credited.

44:44.973 --> 44:46.725
Does she know your screenplay
won the grant?

44:53.399 --> 44:55.859
This needs to be cleared up
from the start.

44:56.443 --> 44:58.404
It'll get messy
if this becomes an issue later.

45:05.411 --> 45:06.787
Goodbye.

45:14.545 --> 45:16.130
Are you less busy now?

45:19.174 --> 45:20.008
Yes.

45:20.676 --> 45:22.010
But I'm about to get busy again.

45:22.094 --> 45:23.720
I'm glad. It's good to be busy.

45:27.474 --> 45:30.060
WEATHER MAKER
BY HWANG DONG-MAN

45:36.483 --> 45:39.653
You still need to eat on time
even if you're busy.

45:40.487 --> 45:43.532
PRODUCER BYEON EUN-A

46:00.299 --> 46:01.550
I'm home.

46:01.633 --> 46:02.885
Are you just getting in?

46:06.430 --> 46:07.556
You're late.

46:28.660 --> 46:30.162
Why haven't you been replying to my texts?

46:38.545 --> 46:39.796
"I got the grant."

46:40.506 --> 46:41.715
"Thanks for your help."

46:44.092 --> 46:46.678
Want me to fill in the parts you left out?

46:48.805 --> 46:50.974
"Don't tell anyone
you were involved in my screenplay,

46:51.058 --> 46:52.893
or that you know me."

46:53.894 --> 46:56.522
"Don't even act like you know me."

47:01.318 --> 47:02.569
I'd appreciate that.

47:04.738 --> 47:06.490
It won't do either of us any good

47:06.573 --> 47:07.699
if word gets out we dated.

47:08.283 --> 47:10.285
That's not what you're afraid of.

47:11.620 --> 47:13.664
You're afraid of people finding out
we wrote it together.

47:14.706 --> 47:16.875
For fuck's sake.

47:20.963 --> 47:22.130
Hey.

47:22.714 --> 47:24.174
I've lost five teeth working on this.

47:24.967 --> 47:26.969
How dare you say we wrote it together?

47:41.608 --> 47:42.609
It really hurts

47:44.111 --> 47:46.363
to wish the worst on someone
I used to like.

47:49.116 --> 47:51.827
It feels like acid
being poured on my heart.

47:55.622 --> 47:56.999
But I won't take it anymore.

48:00.002 --> 48:02.045
Your cursing and violence

48:03.213 --> 48:05.632
made up only 3% of our time together.

48:07.175 --> 48:09.261
But now you're trying to undermine

48:09.344 --> 48:11.638
the other 97% of the time
when we were okay.

48:12.598 --> 48:14.141
So I'll have to respond in kind.

48:18.270 --> 48:20.856
Now all that's left
is that 3% of bitter fighting.

48:28.113 --> 48:29.573
Put my name on the screenplay,

48:30.198 --> 48:31.950
or take out all the parts I wrote.

48:32.826 --> 48:35.954
We exchanged emails,
so you'll know which parts I wrote.

48:40.709 --> 48:42.127
I wish you'd just die.

48:56.975 --> 48:58.727
There are tons of people like you
in this industry.

48:59.394 --> 49:01.438
People who can't write anything
on their own,

49:01.521 --> 49:03.106
yet tell others how to write

49:03.190 --> 49:04.900
and try to go along for the ride.

49:08.195 --> 49:09.279
Is it Hwang Dong-man this time?

49:11.531 --> 49:13.241
I hear you only review leftovers

49:13.867 --> 49:15.535
since you can never get a good one.

49:17.829 --> 49:19.081
Seriously.

49:20.624 --> 49:21.583
Aren't you embarrassed

49:22.501 --> 49:23.877
to be involved with a loser like him?

49:37.974 --> 49:38.892
Damn it!

49:55.075 --> 49:57.035
A man on the verge of success

49:57.119 --> 49:58.704
is easily blinded.

50:01.039 --> 50:02.499
And they can easily become a bad guy.

50:08.338 --> 50:11.758
Everyone here has been through the same.

50:17.514 --> 50:20.225
And everyone is still ashamed
about what they did.

50:21.685 --> 50:23.937
I love that they know how to feel ashamed.

50:27.566 --> 50:29.151
People who remain blinded

50:29.735 --> 50:31.653
and driven by ruthless ambition

50:31.737 --> 50:34.322
and selfish desires are not allowed here.

50:36.158 --> 50:37.367
So what about you?

50:39.411 --> 50:41.329
Will you get yourself banned,

50:41.413 --> 50:43.999
or will you be someone
who lives with shame for a long time?

50:53.091 --> 50:56.428
If you wanted all the credit,
you should've pursued a solo art form,

50:57.471 --> 50:59.431
not filmmaking,
where 200 people collaborate.

52:04.287 --> 52:06.623
I can't believe you said
you were delighted.

52:09.084 --> 52:10.168
I felt my stomach drop.

52:12.045 --> 52:13.630
We have to keep seeing each other,

52:13.713 --> 52:15.423
so you have to watch what you say.

52:16.633 --> 52:18.093
You know he's having a rough time.

52:19.803 --> 52:23.807
I'm not asking for much, am I?

52:23.890 --> 52:26.643
Can't you just be kind to him?

52:28.061 --> 52:29.145
Is that so hard to do?

52:30.105 --> 52:32.315
Kindness is basic human decency, right?

52:33.942 --> 52:35.443
Jeez.

52:36.111 --> 52:36.987
Yeong-su.

52:38.238 --> 52:39.489
I'm really sad.

52:40.365 --> 52:43.243
How could you ask me
to be kind to those guys?

52:43.827 --> 52:45.745
I'm really good at telling

52:47.163 --> 52:50.083
who likes me and who doesn't.

52:51.251 --> 52:52.878
When I'm with someone who likes me,

52:53.503 --> 52:54.796
I become really gentle.

52:55.797 --> 52:56.923
My body responds.

52:57.507 --> 52:59.801
My blood pressure and heart rate drop.

53:00.886 --> 53:03.805
It's an instinctive reaction
that all animals share.

53:04.389 --> 53:05.557
I feel really grateful

53:06.725 --> 53:09.311
when someone chooses to sit next to me
in a coffee shop.

53:09.394 --> 53:11.605
I even put my hands together and pray

53:13.481 --> 53:15.567
that they have a wonderful day.

53:17.944 --> 53:21.615
I'm just mad I don't have enough luck
to make that wish last more than a day.

53:21.698 --> 53:22.866
That's who I am.

53:23.450 --> 53:25.076
If you show me an ounce of kindness,

53:25.160 --> 53:26.912
I'll do anything for you.

53:28.163 --> 53:30.540
So why do I have to be kind to people
who hate me?

53:35.795 --> 53:38.548
I'm not the one you should be talking to.
Talk to those guys!

53:41.217 --> 53:42.052
You know,

53:43.386 --> 53:44.971
I'm like a litmus test strip.

53:45.472 --> 53:47.891
If the other person is acidic,
I'm acidic too.

53:47.974 --> 53:50.143
If they're alkaline, I'm alkaline as well.

53:50.727 --> 53:52.604
You're not aware of this…

53:54.856 --> 53:56.816
but I'm a freaking lovable guy.

54:03.782 --> 54:06.284
They say catching falling leaves
brings good luck.

54:07.661 --> 54:09.579
I'm passing along the luck I caught.

54:18.797 --> 54:22.175
Do you know what my emotion watch says
whenever I see my friends?

54:23.802 --> 54:24.886
Not me.

54:26.930 --> 54:29.099
-He's your senior, right?
-I'm clean.

54:30.850 --> 54:31.685
What's that?

54:34.062 --> 54:37.023
Oh, it's clean because of that?

54:37.107 --> 54:38.441
Come on, that's enough.

54:40.402 --> 54:41.236
"Anxious."

54:43.530 --> 54:44.572
I had no idea

54:45.198 --> 54:46.533
I felt that anxious.

54:48.368 --> 54:49.786
If I wedge myself into a place

54:50.370 --> 54:52.080
where I'm not welcome,

54:52.539 --> 54:53.832
how could I not feel anxious?

54:55.125 --> 54:57.544
So I talk my head off
to overcome that anxiety.

54:58.795 --> 55:01.715
I laugh and talk until tears come out,

55:02.590 --> 55:06.177
but when my emotion watch vibrates,
and I look down at it,

55:07.345 --> 55:08.847
do you know what it says?

55:11.391 --> 55:12.392
"Fed up."

55:12.475 --> 55:14.769
FED UP

55:44.049 --> 55:45.592
How long am I banned for?

55:46.176 --> 55:47.469
Until you get a girlfriend.

55:50.513 --> 55:53.725
That'll knock some sense into you
much faster than wearing that watch.

55:54.559 --> 55:57.062
Talk to a woman. Hug her. Sleep with her.

55:57.145 --> 55:58.188
Then you'll come to your senses.

56:00.023 --> 56:04.611
You're not brave enough
to grow old and die on your own.

56:06.529 --> 56:07.489
So find a woman.

56:18.041 --> 56:19.542
People who like me

56:20.335 --> 56:21.836
ease my anxiety,

56:22.796 --> 56:26.549
so I don't have to act out like crazy.

56:54.786 --> 56:55.912
Eun-a.

56:58.456 --> 57:01.960
RESTRICTED AREA
EMERGENCY MEDICAL CENTER

57:20.895 --> 57:21.938
Grandma.

57:24.524 --> 57:26.151
Do you have a 500-won coin?

57:35.118 --> 57:36.828
When I get nosebleeds…

57:41.499 --> 57:44.127
my whole body hurts
like it's being torn apart.

57:45.920 --> 57:47.881
I'm in excruciating pain one moment…

57:50.175 --> 57:52.260
Don't act like you're the adult here.

57:52.343 --> 57:53.970
Nobody here asked you to.

57:54.053 --> 57:56.764
And just you wait.
I'm about to become something incredible.

57:56.848 --> 57:58.933
Look forward to my shiny story.

58:00.393 --> 58:01.436
Then suddenly,

58:03.021 --> 58:04.189
just like that,

58:05.940 --> 58:07.108
the pain disappears.

58:08.234 --> 58:09.652
As if a knot

58:10.487 --> 58:13.198
just slips loose.

58:14.115 --> 58:16.493
What does your watch say then?

58:20.622 --> 58:21.706
"Relieved."

58:21.789 --> 58:23.666
RELIEVED

59:12.215 --> 59:14.217
Whenever I come across
a similar situation,

59:15.885 --> 59:19.806
I'm right back at that moment,
paralyzed with fear.

59:21.099 --> 59:22.767
Back to when I was helpless.

59:24.686 --> 59:26.980
Back in the classroom
where I couldn't leave.

59:28.565 --> 59:29.899
Back when I was nine.

59:32.485 --> 59:34.904
Back when I couldn't even breathe

59:36.364 --> 59:38.116
in front of the people who crossed me off…

59:40.034 --> 59:42.203
and all I could do
was to helplessly wait for death.

59:44.247 --> 59:45.373
Who do you think it was?

59:47.250 --> 59:48.293
Who do you think

59:48.960 --> 59:50.587
was the first person to cross you off?

01:00:00.930 --> 01:00:01.764
M…

01:00:03.433 --> 01:00:04.350
O…

01:00:06.102 --> 01:00:06.978
T…

01:00:09.105 --> 01:00:09.939
H…

01:00:13.318 --> 01:00:14.694
E…

01:00:14.777 --> 01:00:17.155
MOTHE…

01:00:29.042 --> 01:00:30.460
That word…

01:00:36.090 --> 01:00:37.675
is so overrated.

01:02:06.723 --> 01:02:07.682
Jeez, you scared me.

01:02:30.997 --> 01:02:31.873
Can you guess…

01:02:34.041 --> 01:02:35.376
what just popped up?

01:02:38.755 --> 01:02:39.589
"Shocked."

01:02:40.882 --> 01:02:41.758
"Flustered."

01:02:42.800 --> 01:02:43.676
"Worried."

01:02:45.636 --> 01:02:46.679
It didn't say "excited."

01:02:49.766 --> 01:02:50.600
Gosh, I…

01:02:51.559 --> 01:02:53.478
I was really surprised.

01:02:58.733 --> 01:03:02.028
I'm not a destructive person!

01:03:02.987 --> 01:03:06.032
I'm not a monster!

01:03:33.226 --> 01:03:34.393
Where do you live?

01:03:40.650 --> 01:03:42.693
I'll scatter 500-won coins for you!

01:03:42.777 --> 01:03:44.111
Where do you live?

01:04:12.181 --> 01:04:14.058
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

01:04:32.159 --> 01:04:33.578
Did you see the social media post?

01:04:33.661 --> 01:04:35.872
Her husband raised their kid.
She wasn't neglected.

01:04:35.955 --> 01:04:39.709
One wrong move and Oh Jeong-hui
can kiss her career goodbye.

01:04:40.251 --> 01:04:42.545
-No way.
-Read this, Hwang Dong-man.

01:04:42.628 --> 01:04:44.547
I bet Hwang Dong-man
wants to die right now.

01:04:44.630 --> 01:04:45.756
Damn it!

01:04:45.840 --> 01:04:47.174
Hwang Dong-man, did you read it?

01:04:49.093 --> 01:04:50.428
Where are you going?

01:04:50.511 --> 01:04:52.430
Tell me a funny story.

01:04:52.513 --> 01:04:54.849
Don't fight the thing
that's giving you a hard time, Eun-a.

01:04:54.932 --> 01:04:56.183
It's like sleep paralysis.

01:04:56.267 --> 01:04:57.852
I always chose to avoid them.

01:04:57.935 --> 01:05:00.938
But this time,
I'm going to put them in their place.

01:05:01.022 --> 01:05:02.440
We should meet. Come outside.

01:05:02.523 --> 01:05:06.068
So? Did you choke down every last word?

01:05:08.821 --> 01:05:13.826
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim
